  "articleSummary": "The article argues that LLMs are unreliable for executing deterministic business processes, advocating for workflows to enforce strict step sequences and memory systems to manage context efficiently. It presents a weather activity planner example using the Mastra framework, where a deterministic step fetches weather data before an LLM creatively suggests activities. The tone is a tutorial with a critical edge, framing the solution as knowing when to make the LLM \"obey\" rather than \"think.\" Key technologies include Mastra workflows, semantic memory, and Zod schemas. The intended audience is developers building production-grade LLM agents.",
